Path: This week in Nu #62
Content:
LhKipp added optional 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2685] type inference for the 
``alias``
 command
gillespiecd added a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2696] radix option for str decimal conversion
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2710] rounding precision
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2711] inode information to 
``ls -l``
CBenoit improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2697] passing strings to external commands
fdncred added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2698] some helper methods for working with structured values
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2704] a 
``seq``
 command
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2709] ``char``
 support for arbitrary unicode
, improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2712] rounding
jonathandturner removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2701] it-expansion
, bumped to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2702] 0.21.1
, added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2706] block type inference
jjshanks updated 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2718] required rust version
